"n.残暴，暴行 【英】 n. 残暴，暴行(brutalit y, cruelty) 【记】 atroc(阴沉,兇残)+io us→兇狠的 【例】 The brutal murderer committed a lot of atrocities. n. 暴行(由武装力量对公民或犯人做出的暴力的折磨) = brutality 【例】The murderer committed a lot of atrocities 这个凶手犯了很多暴行. 【记】at在, ro读: 肉, city城市－在血肉横飞的城市－充满了暴行. 【记】atrocious 名词 atrocity (n.)  1530s, from Middle French atrocité or directly from Latin atrocitatem (nominative atrocitas) ""cruelty, fierceness, harshness,"" noun of quality from atrox ""fierce, cruel, frightful,"" from PIE *atro-ek-, from root *ater- ""fire"" (see atrium) + *okw- ""see"" (see eye (n.)); thus ""of fiery or threatening appearance."" The meaning ""an atrocious deed"" is from 1793."
